from transformers import pipeline

summarizer = pipeline("summarization",model="facebook/bart-large-cnn")

long_text = """
The Hugging Face Transformers library provides a simple and consistent API for using a
wide variety of pre-trained models for natural language processing tasks such as text
classification, question answering, and summarization. One of its most powerful features
is the pipeline abstraction, which allows users to perform these tasks with just a few
lines of code. Summarization is the task of shortening a long document while preserving
its key information and overall meaning. Hugging Face offers several models fine-tuned
for summarization, such as BART and T5. These models can be accessed through the
summarization pipeline and can generate high-quality summaries useful for applications
such as news aggregation, document review, and information retrieval.
"""

summary = summarizer(
    long_text,
    max_length=50,
    min_length=10,
    do_sample=False
)

print("Summary:")
print(summary[0]["summary_text"])
